lfld_xGF is a program  for the search for factors of the Generalized FERMAT Numbers (xGF).

1) How LFLD_XGF works:

The search space, defined by k = kstart, ..., kend and n = nstart, ..., nend,
is subdivided into smaller blocks with k = kcurrent, ..., kcurrent+ktep and
n = ncurrent, ..., ncurrent+nstep.

For each smaller block, a sieve is applied to a specified limit.
The remaining candidates are converted to binary and checked. Candidates with 160 bits or 
more undergo a PRP test before verification.
The factors detected are tested when the primality (Proth test) or probable primality.

2) How to use:

Use the command line:
  
     llfd_xGF  [file]

where "file" is the file containing information about the search.
If omitted, the llfd_xGF.ini file is used.

For the definition of the options the following types are used:

  int32: integer between 0 and 32767
  int64: integer between 0 and 2^64. Modifiers are accepted (K : x1000, M : x10^6, G : x10^9, T : 10^12, P : 10^15 and E : 10^18)
  char: character, without quotes or apostrophs.
  strN: string with N character, without quotes or apostrophs

     
The initial file must have the following information:

a) kStart=int64
b) kEnd=int64
c) nStart=int32
d) nEnd=int32

Define the search space: kStart <= k <= kEnd; nStart <= n <= nEnd

e) kStep=int64   [default: kEnd-kStart+1]
f) nStep=int32   [default: nEnd-nStart+1]

Divide the search space into blocks of size kStep by nStep.

Other options are:

g) device=int32 
Define cuda device number to be used. [default: 0]

h) order=char
Define block advance order. The alternatives are: k or n. [default: k]

i) verbose=int32 
Defines the amount of information shown on the screen. [default: 19 (lvRANGE|lvFACTOR|lvDETAILS)] (see below)

j) log=int32 
Defines the amount of information recorded in the log file. [default: 3 (lvRANGE|lvFACTOR)] (see below)

k) debug=int32 
Defines additional information is generated by the program for debugging of the code. [default: 0 (lvNOTHING)] (see below)

l) pMax=int64 
Indicates the highest prime to be used in the sieve of candidates. Defining pMax=0, the program automatically chooses a limit. [default: 0 (auto)]

m) prefix=str127
Prefix used in the name of the files to be saved.

n) kCurrent=int64
   nCurrent=int32
They are options automatically save by the program after each block. Indicate the position of the next block.
Allow to restart the search from a stopping point.

###########################################################################################################################

For the definition of verbose, log and debug levels, just add the values of the desired levels.

// verbose and log levels
lvNOTHING 0    Nothing is shown.
lvFACTOR 1     Shows the factors found.
lvRANGE 2      Show statistics of the block (general).
lvXGF 4        Show statistics of the block (xGF tests).
lvSIEVE 8      Show statistics of the block (sieve).
lvDETAILS 16   Show search evolution in the block.
lvTIME 32      Show time spent at each step.
lvETA 64       Show estimated search ending.

//debug levels 
lvNOTHING 0      Nothing
lvPRIMESSIEVE 1  Saves table of primes used in sieve
lvCANDIDATES 2   Save the remaining candidates after the sieve
lvFILL 4         Save the checked candidates in the basic type (64, 96, ... bits). At the moment, this option is disabled.

###########################################################################################################################

Extensions used in saved files:

(prefix).log      Log level
(prefix).Factors  Factors Found 
(prefix).spt      Sieve prime table
(prefix).(nCurrent).(kCurrent).kt    Candidates table for block
(prefix).(m).scc  Checked candidates in the basic type

The .log, , .Factors and .ini files save automatically a backup copy, preceded by "bkp." .

###########################################################################################################################
